makeotf v2.0.90 gives an error when a feature file uses compact syntax for specifying a Chained contextual substitution (GSUB type 6) that points to a Multiple substitution (GSUB type 2).

Example input:
```
languagesystem latn dflt;
feature test {
    substitute [A-C] f_f_i' [X-Z] by f f i;
} test;
```

Observed: Fails with message “Unsupported contextual GSUB replacement sequence.”
Expected: Should build a GSUB type 6 lookup that is chained to a GSUB type 2 lookup.

Users can work around this with named lookup references. But it seems like a compiler bug, hence the report.

